to that? Do I have to assign points? What's going on here? So with the mapping structures,

502
00:24:40,853 --> 00:24:44,258
the idea is that we have sort of a more open way of visually communicating.

503
00:24:45,362 --> 00:24:46,102
what you're trying to do.

504
00:24:47,082 --> 00:24:49,223
And on the writing side, the goal

505
00:24:49,283 --> 00:24:52,164
is to better communicate options and outcomes to your players

506
00:24:52,284 --> 00:24:52,625
as well.

507
00:24:52,985 --> 00:24:54,265
They won't actually see your map, of course.

508
00:24:54,805 --> 00:24:56,786
But if you can say, oh, well, over here,

509
00:24:56,846 --> 00:24:58,067
this is going to have a major effect,

510
00:24:58,127 --> 00:25:01,568
then you might be able to actually write something

511
00:25:01,608 --> 00:25:02,489
to hint at that.

512
00:25:04,089 --> 00:25:05,730
So the one template I'm going to get to

513
00:25:05,970 --> 00:25:08,391
is this lock and key template, which needs a new name.

514
00:25:08,451 --> 00:25:10,712
So if you have any ideas, let me know, because it implies puzzle.

515
00:25:11,352 --> 00:25:13,013
And it's not supposed to be just puzzles.

516
00:25:13,877 --> 00:25:17,099
It's based just on the idea that the player needs to do X before Y can happen.

517
00:25:17,119 --> 00:25:20,441
It's basically Boolean logic for people who have trouble visualizing flowcharts.

518
00:25:21,702 --> 00:25:22,703
And it's a pretty simple idea.

519
00:25:23,263 --> 00:25:28,426
The idea is you have these numbered nodes, and any set that have the same number, or one unit,

520
00:25:30,536 --> 00:25:34,039
with L and U being locked and unlocked, and K being the key.

521
00:25:34,139 --> 00:25:37,241
So up at the top in the zoomed-in version, we have 2K,

522
00:25:37,681 --> 00:25:40,644
and we have 2L that can get us to 2K, which then lets us

523
00:25:40,704 --> 00:25:41,424
unlock 2U.

524
00:25:42,105 --> 00:25:43,626
And in this case, I put them all near each other

525
00:25:43,686 --> 00:25:45,748
for space saving, but you can have them farther apart.

526
00:25:46,368 --> 00:25:47,529
But the idea is that you actually

527
00:25:47,549 --> 00:25:49,450
have a way of saying, no, these two things are actually

528
00:25:49,530 --> 00:25:52,333
the same, they're just spatially apart.

529
00:25:53,952 --> 00:25:54,913
which might seem a little weird,

530
00:25:55,033 --> 00:25:57,014
but this worked really well with one student group,

531
00:25:57,114 --> 00:25:59,275
the group that actually did the really nice looking video.

532
00:26:00,416 --> 00:26:01,757
They decided to use Twine initially,

533
00:26:01,937 --> 00:26:06,299
and they actually entered the template into Twine,

534
00:26:06,960 --> 00:26:08,661
and then typed in their story idea.

535
00:26:09,681 --> 00:26:11,182
And only after that did they say,

536
00:26:11,202 --> 00:26:13,283
okay, now let's actually start breaking this thing up

537
00:26:13,343 --> 00:26:15,264
and figuring out what do we really wanna tell,

538
00:26:15,304 --> 00:26:16,705
let's throw out this template idea,

539
00:26:16,725 --> 00:26:18,966
and actually make it into something.

540
00:26:20,469 --> 00:26:25,692
What's funny is all their scribbles on the left actually ended up turning into something on the right

541
00:26:25,872 --> 00:26:28,353
that looked very much like the map I'd originally given them.

542
00:26:28,893 --> 00:26:31,914
But that's actually the physical layout of the insane asylum.

543
00:26:32,835 --> 00:26:34,976
The story's about a journalist investigating an insane asylum.

544
00:26:36,014 --> 00:26:38,976
because we still can't quite get away from the broken people,

545
00:26:39,036 --> 00:26:41,538
crazy theme of interactive fiction.

546
00:26:41,798 --> 00:26:43,799
But I think it's actually kind of a cool thing,

547
00:26:43,879 --> 00:26:44,800
so we'll go with it.

548
00:26:45,400 --> 00:26:46,721
Anyway, but what was really cool here

549
00:26:46,881 --> 00:26:48,802
is that whether accidentally or on purpose,

550
00:26:49,343 --> 00:26:50,724
they actually ended up sort of creating

551
00:26:50,764 --> 00:26:54,106
this physical landscape that mapped the mental breakdown

552
00:26:54,146 --> 00:26:56,227
of the woman, sort of the, if she goes one direction,

553
00:26:56,287 --> 00:26:59,149
it's more into she's going to be imprisoned forever.

554
00:26:59,770 --> 00:27:00,730
And if she goes the other direction,

555
00:27:00,750 --> 00:27:01,591
then she might get out.

